'''Fever''' is a poem by [[Suman Pokhrel]]. It was appeared in [[Global Poetry]] in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalpoetry.org/blog/2015/04/01/fever|title=Fever|first=Suman|last=Pokhrel||publisher=Global Poetry}}</ref> Later, this poem has been appeared in other platforms,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ayanipastrami.wordpress.com/2015/04/27/fever-poem-by-suman-pokhrel|title=Fever|first=Suman|last=Pokhrel||publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://wildsoundfestivalreview.com/2015/04/25/fever-poem-by-suman-pokhrel|title=Fever|first=Suman|last=Pokhrel||publisher=Wild Sound Festival Review}}</ref> and the part of it has been quoted in different quotation sites.<ref>http://www.morefamousquotes.com/quotes/2552856-i-want-the-fever-to-grab-me-forever-and.html</ref> <ref>http://www.briefquotes.com/author/Suman%20Pokhrel</ref><ref>https://www.quotes.wiki/i-want-the-fever-to-grab-me-forever-and-want-yo</ref>
This poem is translated into [[French language|French]] as "LA FIÈVRE", and is published in Poetic Prism, an international multilingual poetry anthology, in 2016.<ref>{{Citation|last=Pokhrel|first=Suman|author1-link= |title =LA FIÈVRE|trans-title=Fever|language=French |translator=Laura Mucheli Klemm|journal= Poetic Prism 2016 [International Multilingual Poetry Anthology]|date=September 2016|issu=|page=99|publisher=The Cultural Center of Vijayawada and Amarawati|editor=Padmaja Iyengar|location= Andra Pradesh, India|url =|issn= |doi=|mr=|zbl=}}</ref>
